node_modules/
# Also ignore a node_modules *symlink* (worktree pattern: ln -s <main>/node_modules).
# `node_modules/` matches only directories — a symlink slips through and can be
# committed by accident (regression: a self-referencing symlink landed on staging).
node_modules
packages/*/node_modules
.claude/orchestrator-prompts/*
!.claude/orchestrator-prompts/README.md
# Allow umbrella subdirs back into tracking so done.md closure markers AND
# kickoff design docs can be committed (CLAUDE.md «Umbrella closure convention»,
# #274; cross-session kickoff portability, SSOT #116). kickoff.md is a durable
# committed design doc (joins done.md as a tracked exception); state.md and the
# _plan-cache / _master-backlog-delta runtime files inside subdirs stay ignored
# via the explicit subpath ignore below.
!.claude/orchestrator-prompts/*/
.claude/orchestrator-prompts/*/*
!.claude/orchestrator-prompts/*/done.md
!.claude/orchestrator-prompts/*/kickoff.md
# Stage dispatch chain for the modular-install-fullpack umbrella (S0 boundary
# blueprint + S1-S5 dispatch inputs). Same durable-committed-design-doc class as
# kickoff.md; tracked so kickoff-s0.md reaches `staging` for aif/S1 to read from
# the container base (.claude/rules/kickoff-staging-placement.md §1), and s1-s5
# stay portable across sessions/worktrees (SSOT #116). Per-umbrella glob (not the
# migration-ast per-file form) because this chain has five dispatch stages, not one.
!.claude/orchestrator-prompts/modular-install-fullpack/kickoff-s*.md
*.log
.DS_Store
*.tgz
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Stryker mutation testing output (Wave 9.2)
packages/*/reports/

# AIF (ai-factory / aif-handoff) install scaffolding — tool-generated, per-consumer
# output, never tracked. Without these ignores, aif-handoff's branch-isolation
# dirty-worktree guard (packages/shared/src/gitIsolation.ts → assertWorkingTreeClean)
# sees the installer's own files as uncommitted work and refuses to create/switch
# task branches (BranchIsolationError "dirty_worktree"). Root-anchored to avoid
# touching the framework's own tracked .claude/skills/* entries.
/.ai-factory/
/.ai-factory.json
/.codex/
/.opencode/*
!/.opencode/INSTALL.md
/.claude/agents/
/.claude/skills/aif/
/.claude/skills/aif-*/
# Exception: aif-doctor is a FRAMEWORK-AUTHORED skill (not an AIF-installed one);
# the aif-* glob above is for installer-generated consumer skills. Track it like
# the other framework skills (dispatcher, pipeline).
!/.claude/skills/aif-doctor/

# Stryker mutation-run sandbox (never commit)
packages/core/.stryker-tmp/

# Agnosticism audit — generated conformance record
tests/agnosticism/conformance-record.tsv
